16- *   6. Generate batch_number = {wo_number}-OUT-{NNN} (seq = count+1 per WO+type),
17- *      expiry_date = current_date + item.shelf_life_days (V-PROD-04).
18- *   7. Build catch_weight_details when weight_mode='catch' (variance vs
19- *      item.nominal_weight; soft warning > tolerance).
20- *   8. INSERT wo_outputs (V-PROD-24 batch-unique-per-year enforced by the schema).
21- *   8b. (W9-K-II, F-A04/F-B08) when no caller-supplied lp_id: create the output
22- *       LP in the SAME txn (status received / qa pending, org-default warehouse,
23- *       genealogy parent = first consumed LP, all consumed LPs in
24: *       ext_jsonb.consumed_lp_ids) and back-link wo_outputs.lp_id.
25- *   9. emit production.output.recorded in the SAME txn.
26- *
27- * NUMERIC-exact: qty / per-unit kg never round-trip through a binary float. The
28- * body sends strings; we validate them as decimal strings and pass them straight
29- * to NUMERIC(12,3) columns. Variance math uses a small fixed-point decimal helper
30- * (no `Number()` on the kg values) so two outputs that sum to the same NUMERIC
31- * are bit-identical.
32- *
